Package io.github.JeremyBloom.mosdex2.objectModel

Class MsdxTable

java.lang.Object
io.github.JeremyBloom.mosdex2.objectModel.MsdxObject
io.github.JeremyBloom.mosdex2.objectModel.MsdxTable
public class MsdxTable
extends MsdxObject
Represents a MOSDEX TABLE in Java. Note, TABLE includes the subclasses DATA, VARIABLE, CONSSTRAINT, OBJECTIVE, and TERM, but these have no separate Java representations.

The syntax of MOSDEX: Mathematical Optimization Solver Data EXchange, v 2-0. Copyright Â© 2022 Jeremy A. Bloom

    • replaceInstance

      public MsdxTable replaceInstance​(MsdxDataframe dataframe)
      This method is used when revising an Instance to retrieve solution items from a modeling object. It replaces the Table's Schema and Instance with the Dataframe argument.
      Parameters:
      dataframe -
      Returns:
      this Table
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the Table has both an Instance and a Query

    • createInstance

      public MsdxTable createInstance()
      Creates an Instance from the Table's Query or Initialize field. Removes the Query or Initialize field, since a Table cannot have both an Instance and a Query. If the Table does not have a Schema, one is created from the Query; if the Table already has a Schema, it must be the same as the one generated from the Query.
      Returns:
      this table
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalStateException - if this Table has no Query or if it already has an Instance
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the Table's Schema does not match the Query's
